flowRoot.flowPara: Research is sometimes like a puzzle that can be put together in more than one way. Others need to know how you put the puzzle together, not just what the pieces are.
Research is more than conclusions. It starts with a question. That question leads to another. Eventually a clear picture emerges. But it's the journey that's important.
We believe life is too short to redo other people's research. We can move faster and build better research conclusions as we build on each others research. No man is an island.
Our flagship product, Geungle, is a research system for generational history (a.k.a. genealogy done right).
Ever struggled with research? Tired of having to redo or check the research other people have done? Wish it wasn't so hard to share your work?
Want software that makes research easier?

text.tspan: WE ENVISION A BETTER RESEARCH EXPERIENCE

flowRoot.flowPara: We are a small group of people devoted to promoting quality research and facilitating research collaboration.
Research is hard. But too much effort is spent on keeping track of the little bits of information.

We believe that software should work the way researchers work, not the other way around. We are here to simplify your research experience. Please let us know how we can serve you better! Really. We want to know.

Our company came about because we wanted to keep track of our own family history research. We hunted for software that would help us with it. We couldn't find any. So we decided to do it ourselves, and here we are!
Chris loves to tackle difficult problems and dreams (literally) about making research easier. He is our systems thinker.
Katie loves to solve a good puzzle and thrives on the details. She is also our finance and tax geek and actually enjoys it.
And we like it that way. Being small helps us to move faster and be more responsive to the needs of our customers.
Our company would not be here without the contributions from many in the technological and genealogical communities. We are happy to have a chance to contribute back.

text.tspan: We want to show off your research success and help you through your research struggles.

flowRoot.flowPara: We want to remove the barriers blocking the path to good research and help more people understand and learn how to do good research. We want to help people that are doing great research to do it easier. And we want to help others to get to that point. (We refrain from telling you which category we would put ourselves in.)

We figure that if you're going to spend the time and money to do research, you might as well do it right. We want to help. And after you've done great research, we want to help you share it and show it off. (You want to show it after you've put all that work into it, don't you?)

Our flagship product, Geungle, is a research system for generational history (a.k.a. genealogy done right). It is designed to work the way professional genealogists work and allows collaboration in a way that has never before been possible.
If you want to help make Geungle everything you want it to be, sign up to be included in the beta testing. We will be starting small, but we will let you know when have an opening for you!

No doubt about it, research is hard. But too much time and effort is spent in bookkeeping, and not in putting the pieces together. If we can reduce the time spent on bookkeeping, we will have more time to think about how to put the pieces together. We have taken apart the research process to figure out how to make the process easier for researchers.
